issue.body:
Ideally we'd never need to compare PyArrow versions outside of the [PyarrowVersions](https://github.com/googleapis/python-bigquery/blob/40e4da78bb690ff4c94832321377bb1590e2eeaf/google/cloud/bigquery/_helpers.py#L97) class. We might need to add some additional methods / properties to do this.

issue.title: feat: add support for Dataset.isCaseInsensitive

labels.name: api: bigquery
labels.description: Issues related to the googleapis/python-bigquery API.

labels.name: size: m
labels.description: Pull request size is medium.

issue.body:
This commits add the the `is_case_insensitive` property to the `Dataset` class. 

This property uses the `isCaseInsensitive` field of the [Dataset REST API](https://cloud.google.com/bigquery/docs/reference/rest/v2/datasets#resource:-dataset), allowing the configuration of the case-sensitivity of the BigQuery datasets.

Fixes: https://github.com/googleapis/python-bigquery/issues/1670
